## cp2 progress (teacher scope filter — landed, awaiting review; nothing committed)

### Q3 spec-drift reconciliation (RESOLVED in code)
phase-1.md:1150 shows the scope check as
`if (user.roles.includes('teacher')) { ... }`. **That cannot work in this
codebase** — `AuthContext` (apps/api/.../auth/auth-context.ts) is role-free
by design: it carries only `sessionId`, `userId`, `schoolId`, with a header
comment "Roles and permissions are NOT included — handlers that need them
re-fetch via withTenant" (the no-stale-permissions rationale). So cp2 does
NOT read roles off the JWT/AuthContext. Instead it re-fetches the user +
role grants under withTenant via the established
`assertUserActiveAndHasOneOf(authCtx, ["teacher"])` (apps/api/.../auth/
role-check.ts) — the exact pattern every admin endpoint already uses, just
gated on `teacher` instead of `owner|admin`. This is the one spec-vs-code
divergence flagged in the cp1 plan; it is now reconciled and tested
(getMyScope as admin → 403 proves roles come from the DB, not the token).

